# ğŸš€ **Jenkins CI/CD Pipeline (Declarative)**

This is the recommended industry-standard Jenkins pipeline with:

* Maven Build
* Unit Tests
* Build Docker Image
* Push to ECR OR DockerHub
* Deploy to Kubernetes (optional)

---

# âœ… **Jenkinsfile (complete)**

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    environment {
        // Change according to your setup
        DOCKER_IMAGE = "test-poc"
        DOCKER_TAG = "latest"
        AWS_REGION = "ap-south-1"
        ECR_REGISTRY = "<your_account_id>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com"
    }

    stages {

        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                checkout scm
            }
        }

        stage('Build Maven Project') {
            steps {
                sh './mvnw clean package -DskipTests'
            }
        }

        stage('Unit Tests') {
            steps {
                sh './mvnw test'
            }
            post {
                always {
                    junit '**/target/surefire-reports/*.xml'
                }
            }
        }

        stage('Login to AWS ECR') {
            steps {
                sh '''
                    aws ecr get-login-password --region ${AWS_REGION} \
                    | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin ${ECR_REGISTRY}
                '''
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                sh '''
                    docker build -t ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} .
                    docker tag ${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG} ${ECR_REGISTRY}/${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG}
                '''
            }
        }

        stage('Push Docker Image to ECR') {
            steps {
                sh '''
                    docker push ${ECR_REGISTRY}/${DOCKER_IMAGE}:${DOCKER_TAG}
                '''
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to Kubernetes') {
            when {
                expression { return fileExists('k8s/deployment.yaml') }
            }
            steps {
                sh '''
                    kubectl apply -f k8s/deployment.yaml
                    kubectl apply -f k8s/service.yaml
                    kubectl apply -f k8s/hpa.yaml || true
                '''
            }
        }

    } // stages

    post {
        always {
            echo 'Pipeline finished.'
        }
    }
}
```

---

# ğŸ§© **What This Jenkins Pipeline Does**

| Stage         | Description                         |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Checkout      | Pulls code from GitHub              |
| Build         | mvn package                         |
| Test          | Runs unit tests and reports         |
| AWS ECR Login | Uses `aws-cli`                      |
| Docker Build  | Builds local Docker image           |
| Docker Push   | Pushes to AWS ECR                   |
| K8s Deploy    | Deploys to cluster (if YAML exists) |

